{
  "query": "What are the most beneficial actions for reducing soil erosion in Mediterranean orchards?",
  "relevant_summary": "Planting or maintaining ground cover in orchards or vineyards reduced soil erosion in six replicated, randomized, controlled studies, including studies from Italy and Spain, while one study from France found similar erosion with or without ground cover; an Italian study reported the least erosion under permanent cover crops and the most under temporary cover crops, and multiple studies from Chile and Spain found greater water-stable soil aggregates with seeded cover crops compared to tilled or bare soils (1367). Additional studies from France and the USA showed reduced erosion under cover crops, with one controlled study finding the highest soil stability under a grass cover and a randomized replicated study reporting reduced soil loss with cover crops (897).",
